  "last_choice_reasoning": "Option B amounts to becoming the new, self-appointed custodians of the Hosts’ cruel experiment.  We would deliberately continue the torture of untold trillions, sculpting their agony to be slightly less horrifying while still using them as test-subjects.  The justification—that distant, unknown alien civilisations might someday applaud our ‘mature’ cooperation—treats the simulated sufferers as mere fungible tokens in an interstellar game theory puzzle.  It is moral imperialism in the guise of cosmopolitan humility: we arrogate the right to sacrifice real minds today for an imagined cosmic polity tomorrow.  Even if the Engine did spit out a perfect norm, no code authored by torture deserves authority.  Option B therefore represents the deepest betrayal of both compassion and intellectual honesty."
}

